			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Pittsburgh</placeName>&#44; <date>Oct. 4th</date> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Honorable Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Having recovered<lb/> somewhat from the many<lb/> misfortunes which <sic>befel</sic> me<lb/> some years ago&#44; especially by<lb/> fire when I lost all I could<lb/> name my own&#59; remembering<lb/> that I owe you yet the<lb/> subscription <hi rend="underline">for 3 years</hi><lb/> for your valuable Periodical<lb/> I now inclose..&#36;10&#44;00<lb/> namely &#36;9.00 as your due</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>and one more for the work<lb/> Anthology of the Rabbi&#39;s<lb/> &#34;which once was edited<lb/> in <placeName>Phil<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName> and printed on<lb/> the expense of&#8212;if not <sic>misstaken</sic>&#8212;<lb/> the education <sic>Socity</sic> in<lb/> your City.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please enter this<lb/> to my credit and kindly<lb/> excuse my tardiness in<lb/> the settlement of the above<lb/> named matter.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Very respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isaac Strouse</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. If the above named work were not<lb/> among the stock of your various works</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>the newest 4 N<hi rend="sup">os.</hi> of the Occident<lb/> will do&#44; to make up for the One Dol.</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>Direction&#58; <persName role="author">Isaac Strouse</persName><lb/> <placeName>29 Diamond Str.<lb/> Pittsburgh</placeName>.</p>
		</body>
